4. Types of Cookies
4.1 BE NOT DECEIVED DOES NOT USE COOKIES FOR ANY PURPOSE, INCLUDING ANY OF THE FOLLOWING PURPOSES

authentication and status - may be used to identify you when you visit a website and as you navigate said website, and to determine if you are logged into said website (cookies used for this purpose are: identify cookies);
shopping cart - use cookies to maintain the state of your shopping cart as you navigate websites (cookies used for this purpose are: identify cookies);
personalization - cookies may be used to store information about your preferences and to personalize a website for you (cookies used for this purpose are: identify cookies);
security - cookies used as an element of the security measures used to protect user accounts, including preventing fraudulent use of login credentials, and to protect a website and services generally (cookies used for this purpose are: identify cookies);
advertising - cookies used to help a website to display advertisements that will be relevant to you (cookies used for this purpose are: identify cookies);
analysis - cookies used to help a website analyze the use and performance of their website and services (cookies used for this purpose are: identify cookies); and
cookie consent - cookies used to store your preferences in relation to the use of cookies more generally (cookies used for this purpose are: identify cookies).

6. Managing cookies
6.1 Most browsers allow you to refuse to accept cookies and to delete cookies. The methods for doing so vary from browser to browser, and from version to version. You can however obtain up-to-date information about blocking and deleting cookies via these links:

https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647 (Chrome);
https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enable-and-disable-cookies-website-preferences (Firefox);
https://help.opera.com/en/latest/security-and-privacy/ (Opera);
https://support.microsoft.com/en-gb/help/17442/windows-internet-explorer-delete-manage-cookies (Internet Explorer);
https://support.apple.com/en-gb/guide/safari/manage-cookies-and-website-data-sfri11471/mac (Safari); and
https://privacy.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-10-microsoft-edge-and-privacy (Edge).

6.2 Blocking all cookies will have a negative impact upon the usability of many websites.
6.3 If you block cookies, you will not be able to use all the features on many websites.
